&lt;/section&gt;&lt;p&gt;Statistics on road safety in Great Britain are mostly based on accidents reported to the police via the STATS19 system. This system allows police forces to report all personal-injury accidents to the Department. It does not collect any information about damage-only accidents.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Information on STATS19 can be found in the report form and the guidance document used by the police when completing the form which can be found below.&lt;/p&gt;

